product_name: NYX Professional MakeupDuck Plump Retractable Plumping Lip Liner
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeGive BackQuacking good news! NYX Professional Makeup Duck Plump Retractable Plumping Lip Lineris here. 12 spicy shades for a plump pout. Dual-edged tip, 10-hour wear.
details: DetailsFeaturesSpicy liners for a DUCKING plump pout in all your favorite go-to shadesFrom everyday nudes, to pinks, reds and browns, NYX has the shade for youDesigned with a dual-edged precision tip for easy application every time. Line with the precise tip for sharp, clean lines and use the flat edge to shape and accentuate inner corners for perfect plump lipsFormulated with the same spicy ginger and capsicum as the viral Duck Plump High Pigment Plumping GlossPlump that works overtime for up to 10 HR Wear. Vegan. Cruelty-freeItem 2634384How To UseLine your top and bottom lip with slanted tip edge and use the flat edge side to line the inner corners. CAUTION: EXTREME SENSATION! When pairing with other lip plumping products avoid filling in lips completely.Always read the ingredient list on the product label before use. Please consult the product packaging on the shade level at your local store for detailed product ingredients and application instructions.IngredientsPinkjection: Isododecane, Synthetic Wax, C15-19 Alkane, Isobutylmethacrylate/Bis-Hydroxypropyl Dimethicone Acrylate Copolymer, Silica, Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride, Euphorbia Cerifera Cera / Candelilla Wax, CI 77492 / Iron Oxides, CI 77891 / Titanium Dioxide, CI 77491 / Iron Oxides, CI 77499 / Iron Oxides, Polyglyceryl-3 Diisostearate, Zingiber Officinale Root Oil / Ginger Root Oil, Anthemis Nobilis Flower Extract, Helianthus Annuus Seed Oil / Sunflower Seed Oil, Simmondsia Chinensis Seed Oil / Jojoba Seed Oil, Prunus Amygdalus Dulcis Oil / Sweet Almond Oil, Capsicum Frutescens Fruit Extract, Stearalkonium Hectorite, Vanillyl Butyl Ether, Aluminum Hydroxide, Propylene Carbonate, Lauryl PEG-10 Tris(Trimethylsiloxy)Silylethyl Dimethicone, Tocopherol, Phenoxyethanol (F.I.L. But because the color was great and it didn't dry out my lips, I really liked it. This went on smoothly and stayed in place. It was nice and thin so it applied beautifully and precisely.

reviews.headline: Ouch!
reviews.comments: I realky wanted to love this lip liner. The colors offered are great. But daaaang, theres a delayed reaction in the STING you feel after putting these on ‚Äî mine didn't start until about 20 mins later, and -no joke- I can still feel it stinging 48 hours later (after only one application!) I wish NYX would reformulate this WITHOUT the plumping sting!

reviews.headline: good colors but stings on lips
reviews.comments: it stings on the lips and feels like I ate something spicy, if you have sensitive lips then not the best choice

reviews.headline: Very soft and comfortable to wear
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] NYX has put out yet another high quality product with their new Duck Plumpling Lip Liner. These liners produce a nice plumping effect that isn't too extreme, which I prefer as I have very sensitive skin. I didn't find the tingling sensation extreme at all actually, which I would also prefer in a product like this. It goes on very soft and smooth and is extremely comfortable to wear. I was very surprised as to how much I like this product.

reviews.headline: Would not repurchase
reviews.comments: Not a good shade and not long lasting

faceoff_positive.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Let me just say, NYX absolutely delivered with their Duck Plump Plumping Lip Liner. this liner is my new favorite. It glides on so smoothly, making it easy to define, shape, and even fill in my lips without any tugging. The dual edged precision tip is genius it feels like it was made for those of us who want to look like we've got our lives together even if we just woke up.

the plumping effect- I don't know what kind of magic they've packed in here (OK, it's the ginger and capsicum), but my lips felt fuller almost immediately. And the best part? It's not that uncomfortable, over-the-top tingling it's just the right amount of spicy to let you know it's working. I wore this liner for hours, and my lips stayed plump and defined the whole time. It's giving 10/10 longevity.
The shade range is gorgeous, and I love that they threw in a bonus "DUCKING CLEAR" shade. It's perfect for those minimal makeup days or when I want a natural but plump pout.
The packaging? Love it. The retractable design is super convenient no sharpening needed‚Ä¶. (because who has time for that?). Plus, it's vegan and cruelty free, which is always a win in my book.
If you're into a liner that does it all plumps, defines, lasts and keeps your lips looking kissable this is the one.
faceoff_positive.headline: Plump lips all day

faceoff_negative.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] At first swipe, I wasn't too impressed with the NYC lip liner cause the formula felt quite dry and tugged uncomfortably on my lips, leaving behind a patchy finish. However, after warming the tip on the back of my hand and giving it a few more tries, I was pleasantly surprised because the texture much smoother with a velvety glide that applied evenly without any dragging.
One thing to note is that this liner sets very quickly. You really don't get any playing time, so blending with a finger or making adjustments is nearly impossible once it's on. The staying power is good, not completely transfer-proof cause it has very minimal transfer so it is long wearing. 
In terms of plumping, I did notice a tingling sensation immediately upon applying, but I honestly didn't notice any plumping. Overall, once you get past the initial dryness and learn how to work with it, this liner performs well, especially for the price. I just wouldn't buy it personally because I am not really able to play and blend it out immediately after applying it. I can see how someone with fuller lips might enjoy it because it does apply smoothly.
faceoff_negative.headline: Not bad, just not for me
